author: maria.m.hynes@gmail.com
fields.title: My First Post
fields.content: Hi guys, Lissaniska is beautiful. If you haven't been in a while, you should take some time out and visit. Oughtarard has some great places to eat and there are endless things to do all around Galways and Mayo and the beautiful Connemara. We are so lucky! What better way to wake up in the morning than looking out at the stunning, peaceful view of Lough Corrib??! Take a look at my early morning photo, amazing weather for the autumn mid-term school break. Makes you just want to go there?

author: maria@databasis.ie
fields.title: Always sunny!
fields.content: It feels like it's always sunny in Le Rouret, but especially if you go there in August.

author: maria.m.hynes@gmail.com
fields.title: Christmas in Le Rouret
fields.content: I think it would be strange to be looking out at the pool and not to be able to use it. The kids would go mad! So mental note...don't go to Le Rouret in the Winter unless the kids are staying at home!

author: maria.m.hynes@gmail.com
fields.title: French Winter
fields.content: I expected it to be mainly deserted in the little village during the winter months but it was incredibly lively! The Christmas Market was full of interesting gift ideas and the Christmas lights around the square were better than anything I've seen. I would love to make it back next year.

author: maria.m.hynes@gmail.com
fields.title: Craft Fairs & Markets
fields.content: I was surprised at the wide variety of craft fairs around Provence. I don't know why now, why I should be surprised. I guess, in my narrow way, I thought that Ireland had cornered the market on craftiness.

fields.comment: I like this place for breakfast. It's small and can be a little cold (the place, not the food!). I am not the biggest fan of the coffee, but if you are a coffee-connoisseur you may very well like it!
We ate here for breakfast twice on the last holiday. It is great for kids, great value and is warm and cozy. The have free coffee refills which is always nice!
It's been a while since we ate in the restaurant but we have eaten in the cafe part. Don't let your eyes trick you into ordering a cake each!
Got a delicious panini here at lunchtime.
Good 'ol SuperMacs. I have never eaten there.
There's a great selection of frocks in this boutique.
Has anyone any opinions on this place?

For what it's worth, this place is only great if you can't remember the details. So, go there after having a glass of wine and you'll probably like it. I just found the place too fussy and the staff made me feel that they were doing me a favour by serving me!
This would be the nearest supermarket, down in Opio. One of the good things is that there is a little pastry shop right next door!
This store in Rochfort has been recently renovated. I would recommend this one.
I tend to agree with that comment because I had a similar experience.
Sorry, I don't think this place was open when I last visited. What do they sell? Dentures?!

You can't go wrong with Londis. It has a car park for starters. You just have to drive in at speed so the kids don't see that it's right beside the playground. They have trolleys and those baskets on wheels, though it usually a nightmare to manoever them around the tiny aisles. It can be a bit crowded at the till with all the special offers in the way, but all in all I like the place. The staff were very friendly last Halloween when I went in desparate to find double-sided sticky tape.
